title: Baharestan County
text: Baharestan County () is a <a href="Counties%20of%20Iran">county</a> in <a href="Tehran%20Province">Tehran Province</a> in <a href="Iran">Iran</a>. The capital of the county is <a href="Golestan%2C%20Iran">Golestan, Golestan District</a>. The county has two districts: <a href="Golestan%20District">Golestan District</a> and <a href="Central%20District%20%28Baharestan%20County%29">Boostan District</a>. The county has three cities: <a href="Golestan%2C%20Iran">Golestan</a>, <a href="Nasimshahr">Nasimshahr</a> and <a href="Salehieh">Salehieh</a>. The county was formed in 2011 from the <a href="Central%20District%20%28Baharestan%20County%29">Boostan District</a> and <a href="Golestan%20District">Golestan District</a>, of <a href="Robat%20Karim%20County">Robat Karim County</a>. At the 2016 census, the county's population was 536,329, in 156,791 households.
